 {"id":"bd-jllnz","title":"PORT: __cxa_thread_atexit + __cxa_tm_cleanup + __cxa_vec_ctor/dtor/cleanup","description":"Add 5 more Itanium C++ ABI primitives to close the rest of the safe-to-implement cxa gaps. (1) __cxa_thread_atexit — trivial public-name wrapper around our existing __cxa_thread_atexit_impl. (2) __cxa_tm_cleanup — no-op for the long-deprecated Transactional Memory cleanup hook (binaries rarely use TM but link-edit needs the symbol). (3) __cxa_vec_ctor(array, count, size, ctor, dtor) — iterate forward and invoke ctor on each element. (4) __cxa_vec_dtor(array, count, size, dtor) — iterate REVERSE and invoke dtor on each element (Itanium contract). (5) __cxa_vec_cleanup(array, count, size, dtor) — same as vec_dtor; called from EH unwind. NULL ctor/dtor pointers must be tolerated (compiler omits them when the type is trivial).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T15:08:30.246634733Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T15:12:04.648545887Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T15:12:04.646461180Z","close_reason":"shipped: 5 more cxa primitives (__cxa_thread_atexit, tm_cleanup, vec_ctor/dtor/cleanup) + 6 abi tests covering forward/reverse iteration + NULL tolerance","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
